	abstract = {Droplet deformation by air cushioning prior to impact is considered. A model is presented coupling the free-surface deformation of a droplet with the pressure field in the narrow air layer generated as a droplet approaches an impact. The model is based upon the density and viscosity in the air being small compared with those in the liquid. Additionally, the Reynolds number, defined using the droplet radius ℛ and approach velocity
              
                
              
              
